Notes__.DepthInfo: Notes: negative water table depths denote surface water, depth to peat. No 3 cm temperatures- soil temps denote water temperature.  | Notes (additional): Forgot one set of 47 mm filter papers, so DOC samples were filtered at lab on July 12, ~16:00 from collected whole water samples. Eriophorum and sphagnum cores suffered a fair deal of compression, though difficult to quantify. Will likely need to use Wardenaar next time- will cause time constraint. Pore water sampling is quite time consumptive. Will not be able to 'suck' and core in the same day with only 2 ppl. If using Waardenaar. When collecting extra 1 cm section for bulk isotope/biogeochem samples, S and D was always 1 cm below microbial interval, M was always 1 cm above microbial interval. Bulk samples were refrigerated over night and split on the morning of the 13th. One should not use field styrofoam vial rack in -80 freezer if it has been a wet day. Instead one should dry the vials and transfer to new, dry cylinder rack. They freeze very tightly in place and make a mess of the foam when removing to tranfer into cryo-box.
